4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE PETROLEUM
5 TANK RELEASE COMPENSATION BOARD; ESTABLISHING PROCEDURES FOR REIMBURSEMENT OF
6 PREVENTATIVE MEASURES; PROVIDING A DISCRETIONARY MEETING UPON ON RELEASE;
7 PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING SECTIONS 75-11-309, 75-11-313, AND 75-11-318,
8 MCA; PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Procedures for reimbursement of preventative measures. (1) Subject
13 to the availability of money from the fund provided for in 75-11-307(6) and in accordance with rules adopted by
14 the board, an owner or operator of a Montana facility that is actively dispensing petroleum must be reimbursed
15 by the board for the following preventive measures:
16 (a) removal of inactive tanks;
17 (b) upgraded automatic tank gauges;
18 (c) piping replacements for single-walled product piping;
19 (d) replacement of single-wall steel tanks for underground tank systems that are 20 years old or
20 older;
21 (e) replacement of single wall fiberglass reinforced plastic tanks that are 20 years old or older;
22 (f) underground storage tank removal investigations for aging tanks nearing 30 years old that
23 have been in compliance; and
24 (g) preventative inspections, including compliance and walk-through inspections.
25 (2) The board shall reimburse an owner or operator up to $2,000 a facility every 1,000 days.
26 (3) (a) The owner or operator shall document in the manner required by the board all preventive
27 measures and submit them for reimbursement to the board in the form and manner required by the board.
28 (b) The owner or operator shall submit one claim for all costs for the 1,000 days following the
