8 Section 2. Section 75-11-309, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "75-11-309. Procedures for reimbursement of eligible costs -- corrective action plans. (1) An
10 owner or operator seeking reimbursement for eligible costs and the department shall comply with the following
11 procedures:
12 (a) If an owner or operator discovers or is provided evidence that a release may have occurred
13 from the owner's or operator's petroleum storage tank, the owner or operator shall immediately notify the
14 department of the release and conduct an initial response to the release in accordance with state and federal
15 laws and rules to protect the public health and safety and the environment.
16 (b) Except for a tank for which a permit is sought under 75-11-308(1)(b)(iii) and that is closed
17 within 120 days of discovery of the release, following discovery of the release, the petroleum storage tank must
18 remain in compliance with applicable state and federal laws and rules that the board determines pertain to
19 prevention and mitigation of petroleum releases.
20 (c) The owner or operator shall conduct a thorough investigation of the release and, subject to
21 subsection (1)(d), report the findings to the department, and, as determined necessary by the department,
22 prepare and submit for approval by the department a corrective action plan that conforms with state, tribal
23 (when applicable), and federal corrective action requirements.
24 (d) For a release in which the costs are expected to exceed $100,000, an owner or operator, a
25 representative of the owner or operator, the department, the board, and board staff shall may meet to discuss
26 the response to the release. For a release in which the costs are expected to be less than $100,000, an owner
27 or operator, a representative of the owner or operator, the department, the board, and board staff may meet to
28 discuss the response to the release if any party requests a meeting.
