4 Section 4. Section 75-11-318, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "75-11-318. Powers and duties of board. (1) The board shall administer the petroleum tank release
6 cleanup fund in accordance with the provisions of this part, including the payment of reimbursement to owners
7 and operators. The board may hire its own staff to assist in the implementation of this part.
8 (2) The board shall determine whether to approve reimbursement of eligible costs under the
9 provisions of 75-11-309(3) and costs of preventative measures under [section 1], shall obligate money from the
10 fund for approved costs, and shall act on requests for the guarantee of payments through the procedures and
11 criteria provided in 75-11-309.
12 (3) The board may conduct meetings, hold hearings, undertake legal action, and conduct other
13 business that may be necessary to administer its responsibilities under this part. The board shall meet at least
14 quarterly for the purpose of reviewing and approving claims for reimbursement from the fund and conducting
15 other business as necessary.
16 (4) The board shall use the fund to pay for:
17 (a) department expenses incurred in providing assistance to the board. The board shall review and
18 comment on all department administrative budget proposals that are assessed against the fund prior to
19 submittal of the department budget for legislative approval. Department administrative expenses on behalf of
20 the board may include:
21 (i) the review or preparation of corrective action plans;
22 (ii) the oversight of corrective action undertaken by owners and operators for the purposes of this
23 part; and
24 (iii) the actual and necessary administrative support provided to the board.
25 (b) department of transportation staff expenses used for the collection of the petroleum storage
26 tank cleanup fee;
